#### Stringify with custom column names/headers

Specifying custom columns is easy in many forms, like just pass `{ columns: [ { key: '', header: '' } ] }` as options.

Or `{ columns: ['name', 'email'] }`.

Or `{ columns: { name: 'Name', email: 'Email' } }`.

```javascript
